      "bullets": [
        "Implementing rsync in Go mitigates legacy C vulnerabilities, protecting against buffer overflows and memory corruption without sacrificing performance.",
        "A stripped-down feature set slashes attack surface by avoiding complex, historically vulnerable rsync protocol extensions and parsing logic.",
        "Go’s strict bounds checking and type safety secure file transfers against remote code execution risks common in native binaries."
